<paragraph pageNumber="15">Type species</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Ventichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="biospeedoi">Ventichthys biospeedoi</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(type locality: South East Pacific Rise, 17º25.38’S, 113º12.29’W, 2586 m).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="15">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="15">An ophidiid genus with robust body; very small, overlapping scales on head and body; thick skin; posteriorly placed, enlarged kidneys; four lateral lines; dorsal fin origin above tip of pectorals; base of pelvic fin below hind margin of opercle; head broad with blunt snout; strong opercular spine covered by thick skin; upper jaw ends just behind eye; teeth granular, one median basibranchial tooth patch; anterior gill arch with 10-11 long rakers; number of rays in dorsal fin 80-89, caudal fin 8, anal fin 64-72, pelvic fin 2, pectoral fin 24-25; number of vertebrae 16-17 + 36 (in total 52-53).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="15">Similarity</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="15">
A phylogenetic analysis of the Ophidiidae needs to be made, but there are two genera, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:6467DD6E-CAFE-423C-B15C-7DF9F6BABE78" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Benthocometes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Benthocometes Goode &amp; Bean 1896:327" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Benthocometes (Goode and Bean, 1886)</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:24013EF6-0125-478B-BEF7-CB33B201FEE1" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Petrotyx" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Petrotyx Heller &amp; Snodgrass 1903:222" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Petrotyx Heller and Snodgrass, 1903</taxonomicName>
that are similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Ophidiidae" genus="Ventichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophidiiformes" pageNumber="15" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ventichthys</taxonomicName>
in having a blunt snout, no free pectoral fin rays, granular teeth, and one basibranchial tooth patch. The differences between the three genera are shown in Table 2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="15">Etymology</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="15">Vent refers to the hydrothermal vent and ichthys to fish.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
